AN ACT relating to courts; revising provisions relating to the
jurisdiction of justice courts in certain criminal cases; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law provides that, with certain exceptions, in criminal cases, the
2 jurisdiction of a justice of the peace extends to the limits of the county of the justice
3 of the peace. (NRS 4.370) This bill creates an additional exception that extends the
4 jurisdiction of a justice of the peace in the case of an arrest made by a member of
5 the Nevada Highway Patrol.
